	<text>
		<body>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Syracuse</placeName>&#44; <date>Monday&#44; 6<hi rend="sup">th</hi> <add>&#63;</add></date>.</p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><date>&#40;July&#41; 1854</date>.</p>
				<p>May the Lord comfort his pious ones in<lb/> accordance with the multitude of his<lb/> favors&#59; and all those who mourn for the<lb/> captivity of <placeName>Jerusalem</placeName>.  May they see the<lb/> rebuilding of the house of the living God&#44;<lb/> and among them my friend the wise etc. <persName>Isaac<lb/> Leeser</persName>.</p>
				<p>Dear Friend&#58;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">This week I <del>received a letter</del> learned from a<lb/> friend in <placeName>Cincinnati</placeName> that my letter about<lb/> <persName>Lilienthal</persName> and which appeared in the &#8220;Occi&#45;<lb/>dent&#8221; was copied in other German news&#45;<lb/>papers.  I believe also in the &#8220;Judenzeitung.&#8221;<lb/>  I am very curious to see and to know <del>under</del><lb/> with what intention it was copied.  You<lb/> will therefore oblige me greatly if you<lb/> had the kindness to send me this news&#45;<lb/>paper.  Please do me this favor.  I am<lb/> always ready to do you a service in<lb/> return.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Respectfully&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Issachar Baer</persName>&#44; son of <persName>Rabbi<lb/>J</persName>&#8212;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName role="author">Dr. B. Illowy</persName>.</p>
		</body>
